<TEXT>
BARCLAYS BANK has appointed Mr Malcolm Levitt (pictured) as its European
Community adviser in succession to Dr Tom Soper who is retiring. Mr Levitt
will advise Barclays on the implications of all aspects of EC policy making
and practices and will represent the bank's views to the EC. He has been a
partner in the European practice of Ernst &amp; Young's management consultancy
since 1987, and gained experience of EC matters as a head of division at the
EC's directorate-general for economic and financial affairs from 1977-80. Mr
Levitt is a former senior economic adviser at the Treasury.
