FT  26 APR 91 / Technology (Worth Watching): Elf research crosses channel
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CLIVE COOKSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ELF AQUITAINE, the French oil and chemicals group, is to set up a
Geosciences Research Centre in London, writes Clive Cookson.
The centre, with 18 researchers and a budget of Pounds 4m a year, will have
three related research programmes: in geology, seismics and reservoir
engineering. There will be a strong focus on three-dimensional computer
modelling, using supercomputers.
Elf says the research will be 'open'. Olivier Guillon, manager of the
centre, will be looking for collaboration from other oil companies operating
in the UK and from university geoscientists.
The establishment of the centre is a sign of Elf's efforts to
internationalise its research and development activities. At present only 20
per cent of the group's FFr4.3bn (Pounds 430m) a year R&amp;D budget is spent
outside France.
