FT  26 APR 91 / International Company News: Bulk of BCE gain comes from
telephone offshoot
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
BCE, the telecommunications holding company, reported higher first-quarter
earnings with larger contributions from Bell Canada, the telephone utility,
and Northern Telecom, the equipment manufacturer.
The Canadian company's earnings were CDollars 293m (USDollars 252.5m), or 88
cents a share, up 11 per cent from CDollars 265m, or 82 cents, a year
earlier. Revenues were CDollars 4.7bn, against CDollars 4.4bn.
Bell Canada contributed CDollars 227m, or 74 cents a share, against CDollars
220m, or 73 cents, a year earlier, and paid preferred dividends of CDollars
17m in both periods.
Its local service revenues were up 4 per cent but long-distance fell 2.6 per
cent because of a slow economy. Operating expenses dipped 3 per cent.
Montreal Trustco and TransCanada PipeLines made lower contributions.
Shell Canada posted a CDollars 35m loss in the first quarter, blaming a
sharp drop in refined products prices and the recession. A year earlier it
earned CDollars 63m, or 56 cents.
The company will continue rationalisation while spending heavily to develop
the big Caroline natural gas field in Alberta. This should be generating
revenue early in 1993.
United Westburne, controlled by Lyonnaise des Eaux of France, had a
first-quarter loss of CDollars 8.2m on revenues of CDollars 489m, against a
profit of CDollars 2m, or 5 cents a share, a year earlier on revenues of
CDollars 591m.
The wholesale plumbing, heating and electrical supplies group will continue
regional expansion in the US.
The shutdown of two Ontario uranium mines and weak metals distribution
markets reduced Rio Algom's sales and earnings in the first quarter.
But the company's potash operations improved with better international
prices while higher production increased returns from Rio's western coal
venture.
Overall, the main Canadian arm of Britain's RTZ Group earned CDollars 14m,
or 31 cents a share, down from CDollars 20.1m, or 44 cents, a year earlier,
on sales of CDollars 265m, against CDollars 355m.
Copper earnings were stable, while the tin mining operation offset lower
prices with higher output.
