   By CLARE PEARSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Northern Telecom, the Canadian telephone equipment maker, has sold the
electrical equipment distribution arm of STC, its recently-acquired UK
subsidiary, to CDME, the French electrical wholesaling company.
Consideration for the sale, which is the result of an auction, is not being
