FT  26 APR 91 / Reactor hopes
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NUCLEAR Electric's ageing reactors will stand a better chance of winning a
new lease of life if, as expected, one of them breaks a world performance
record this afternoon.
The Magnox reactor, at Oldbury-on-Severn nuclear power station in Avon, will
have been operating continuously for 700 days.
Nuclear Electric has six other Magnox reactors, the oldest type of
commercial reactor in the world.
Oldbury's unbroken performance will help to support Nuclear Electric's case
for keeping the seven Magnox reactors going, rather than retiring them at
the conclusion of their thirty-year official life span.
